{[%mdl 8192] B13: Caro-Kann: Exchange Variation and Panov-Botvinnik Attack} 1.
e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bg4 {White has a very active
position} 6. Bb5+ $146 (6. h3 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 Nc6 (7... e6 8. Bd3 Nc6 9. Ne2 Be7
10. O-O O-O 11. c3 a6 12. Bf4 b5 13. b4 Qd7 14. Qe3 Rfc8 15. Nc1 a5 16. Bxb5
axb4 17. cxb4 Bxb4 18. Nd3 Bd6 19. Ne5 Bxe5 20. Bxe5 Qe7 21. Qg5 h6 22. Qh4 {
Brih,S (2220)-Bernard,V (2248) France 2003 0-1 (60)}) 8. Bb5 e6 9. O-O a6 10.
Bxc6+ bxc6 11. Bg5 Be7 12. Na4 O-O 13. c3 h6 14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Qg3 Be7 16. b4
Bd6 17. f4 a5 18. Nc5 axb4 19. cxb4 Bxc5 20. dxc5 Qf6 {Hrabe,P (2310)
-Knazovcik,L (2260) Czechia 2000 1/2-1/2 (49)}) (6. Be2 Nc6 7. O-O e6 8. Bf4
Be7 9. Ne5 Bxe2 10. Nxe2 O-O 11. c3 Nxe5 12. Bxe5 b5 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Nf4 b4
15. Qg4 bxc3 16. bxc3 Rc8 17. Rac1 Bg5 18. Rc2 Bxf4 19. Qxf4 Qb6 20. Rfc1 Rc4 {
Haznedaroglu,K (2287)-Rausis,I (2486) Haarlem 2000 0-1 (43)}) (6. Bg5 a6 7. Be2
Bxf3 8. Bxf3 e6 9. O-O Be7 10. Ne2 Nc6 11. c4 O-O 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. cxd5 exd5
14. Qb3 Nxd4 15. Nxd4 Bxd4 16. Rad1 Qf6 17. Qxd5 Rfd8 18. Qb3 g6 19. Rd2 Rd7
20. Rfd1 Rad8 {De Vos,N (2221)-Kabos,T (2294) Brasschaat 2013 1/2-1/2 (46)})
6... Nc6 7. Bxc6+ bxc6 {Black has the pair of bishops} 8. h3 {White threatens
to win material: h3xg4} Bh5 9. g4 Bg6 {Black has a cramped position. Black's
piece can't move: f8} 10. Ne5 {White threatens to win material: Ne5xc6} Qc8 (
10... Nd7 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Bf4 $11) 11. Nxg6 (11. h4 $142 $5 h6 12. Bf4 $16)
11... hxg6 $11 {Black has new doubled pawns: g6+g7} ({Not} 11... fxg6 12. O-O
$14) 12. Bf4 $2 (12. Qf3 $5 $11 {must be considered}) 12... Nxg4 (12... Qxg4
13. Qxg4 Nxg4 14. Kf1 $17) 13. Qf3 Nf6 14. O-O-O Qf5 15. Rde1 $4 {strolling
merrily down the path to disaster} (15. Qe3 $142 $17) 15... g5 $19 16. Ne2 gxf4
17. Ng3 Qd7 18. Qxf4 e6 19. Re3 (19. h4 {is not the saving move} Rc8 $19) 19...
Bd6 20. Qg5 Bxg3 (20... Kf8 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} 21. Rf3 $19) 21.
fxg3 (21. Qxg7 {is not much help} Ke7 22. Qxg3 Rag8 $19) 21... Ke7 22. g4 Rh6 (
22... Kf8 $142 {seems even better} 23. Rf1 $19) 23. Qe5 (23. Rf1 {cannot
change destiny} Rg6 24. Qh4 $19) 23... Qd6 (23... Nxg4 {and Black can already
relax} 24. Qg5+ Nf6 25. Rb3 $19) 24. Qf5 $4 {but even a better move would not
have saved the game} (24. Qxd6+ $142 Kxd6 25. g5 $19) 24... Ne4 $19 25. Qf3 (
25. Qe5 {cannot change what is in store for White} Qxe5 26. dxe5 Nf2 $19) 25...
Rf6 26. Qg2 (26. Qe2 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} Rf2 27. Qd3 c5 $19)
26... Qf4 (26... Rf2 $142 {and Black has reached his goal} 27. Qf3 Rxf3 28.
Rxf3 e5 $19) 27. Rhe1 Qf2 (27... Nd6 $142 {might be the shorter path} 28. Qg3
Qxd4 29. g5 $19) 28. Qh1 (28. Qxf2 {desperation} Rxf2 29. Rb3 $19) 28... Qd2+
29. Kb1 Rf2 30. Rb3 Qxc2+ 31. Ka1 Kd6 (31... Qc4 {seems even better} 32. Qg1
$19) 32. Rc1 Qe2 33. Re1 (33. Qd1 {does not improve anything} Qxd1 34. Rxd1 g5
$19) 33... Rh2 (33... Qc4 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} 34. Qg1 $19) 34. Qg1
Qf2 35. Rb7 (35. Qxf2 {does not help much} Rxf2 36. Rc1 g5 $19) 35... a5 (35...
c5 $5 {and Black can already relax} 36. Qxf2 Rxf2 37. dxc5+ Nxc5 38. Rb5 $19)
36. Rxf7 (36. Qxf2 {there is nothing else anyway} Rxf2 37. Rc1 $19) 36... Qxb2#
0-1

