2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Nf3 {Black is behind in
developement. Black's piece can't move: c8} (6. Bg5 a6 7. Qd2 Ne5 8. f4 Nc4 9.
Bxc4 Qxc4 10. O-O-O Bb4 11. Nde2 f6 12. Bh4 Nh6 13. g4 O-O 14. g5 fxg5 15. Bxg5
Nf7 16. Bh4 Nd6 17. Qe3 Rf7 18. Kb1 Nb5 19. Rd3 Nxc3+ 20. Nxc3 b5 {Milos,G 
(2560)-Granda Zuniga,J (2590) Buenos Aires 1993 1/2-1/2 (54)}) (6. a3 a6 7. g3
Nf6 8. Nb3 Be7 9. Bg2 O-O 10. O-O d6 11. f4 Rb8 12. Be3 b5 13. Qe2 Bb7 14. g4
Nd7 15. Qf2 Na5 16. Nxa5 Qxa5 17. g5 Rfe8 18. Bd4 Qc7 19. h4 Bf8 20. Rae1 Bc6 {
Soukal,R (2199)-Novak,P (2254) Czechia 2001 1/2-1/2 (45)}) 6... Nf6 $146 {
White has an active position} (6... a6 7. a3 Nf6 8. Bd3 Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Qe2
d6 11. h3 b5 12. Bg5 Bb7 13. Rfe1 Rfe8 14. Rad1 b4 15. Nb1 Nd7 16. Bxe7 Rxe7
17. c3 bxc3 18. Nxc3 Nde5 19. Nxe5 Nxe5 20. Bb1 Rc8 21. Rd4 {Pihajlic,A (2175)
-Maric,A (2365) Pula 1989 0-1 (40)}) 7. Be2 {Black's piece can't move: c8} Bb4
{White has an active position} 8. O-O (8. Qd3 $5 $11) 8... Bxc3 $15 9. bxc3
Nxe4 10. Bb2 O-O {Black castles and improves king safety} 11. Bd3 Nf6 (11... f5
12. c4 Nc5 13. Qd2 $17) 12. c4 (12. Ba3 Re8 13. Bd6 Qa5 $11 (13... Qxd6 $4 14.
Bxh7+ Kxh7 15. Qxd6 $18)) 12... e5 $15 {Black has a new backward pawn: d7.
Black's piece can't move: c8} 13. Re1 Re8 14. Qe2 (14. c5 b6 15. Bb5 bxc5 16.
Bxc6 Qxc6 17. Nxe5 Qa4 $15) 14... d6 15. c5 (15. Rab1 b6 $17) 15... Bg4 (15...
d5 16. Nd4 (16. Bxe5 $2 {is a blank shot} Nxe5 17. Nxe5 Ng4 18. Nxg4 Rxe2 19.
Bxe2 Qxc5 $19) 16... Nxd4 17. Bxd4 $17) 16. cxd6 Qxd6 17. Be4 (17. Bb5 Re6 18.
h3 Nd4 19. Bxd4 exd4 $17) 17... Nd4 (17... Bxf3 18. Bxf3 e4 19. Bxf6 gxf6 20.
Bh5 $17 (20. Bxe4 $2 {is inferior since it leads to} f5 $19)) 18. Qd3 Rad8 (
18... Bxf3 $142 19. Bxf3 Nxf3+ 20. Qxf3 e4 $17) 19. Ng5 $2 (19. Bxd4 $142 Nxe4
20. Rxe4 Bxf3 21. Qxf3 exd4 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 23. Qxb7 $15) 19... h6 $4 {spoils
everything} (19... Nxe4 $5 20. Nxe4 Qc6 21. Bxd4 Rxd4 22. Qe3 $19) 20. Nxf7 $4
{not a good decision, because now the opponent is right back in the game} (20.
Bh7+ $142 {and the scales tip in favour of White} Nxh7 21. Qxh7+ Kf8 22. Ne4
$18) 20... Kxf7 $17 21. Bxd4 (21. Bg6+ Kg8 22. Bxd4 Qxd4 23. Bxe8 Qxd3 24. cxd3
Rxe8 $17) 21... Qxd4 (21... Nxe4 $5 22. Rxe4 Qg6 23. Rae1 $19) 22. Bg6+ Kf8 23.
Qa3+ $4 {sad, but how else could White save the game?} (23. Bxe8 $142 Qxd3 24.
cxd3 Rxe8 25. Rab1 $19) 23... Re7 24. h3 Be6 (24... Be2 $142 {might be the
shorter path} 25. Rab1 Ba6 26. Re3 $19) 25. Rad1 (25. c3 {is still a small
chance} Qd5 26. Qxa7 $19) 25... Qxd1 26. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 27. Kh2 b6 28. Qf3 Rd8 29.
Be4 (29. a4 {hardly improves anything} Bf7 30. Bxf7 Kxf7 $19) 29... Bxa2 30. g4
(30. Bf5 {cannot undo what has already been done} Rd4 31. Qc3 Bc4 $19) 30...
Bd5 31. Bxd5 Rxd5 32. h4 (32. Kg1 {does not solve anything} Kf7 $19) 32... e4 (
32... Rd4 $142 $5 {makes it even easier for Black} 33. Kh3 Rxg4 34. Qe3 $19)
33. Qf4 {[%cal Yg4g5] White intends g5} Ree5 34. g5 (34. c4 {the last chance
for counterplay} Rc5 35. Kg3 $19) 34... hxg5 35. hxg5 (35. Qc1 {a last effort
to resist the inevitable} gxh4 36. Qf4 $19) 35... Rxg5 36. Qb8+ Kf7 37. Qxa7+
Kg6 38. Qxb6 (38. Qb8 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the game} Rd2 39.
Kh1 Rxf2 40. Qd6 e3 41. Qd3+ Kh6 42. Qd6 e2 43. Qb4 Rh5+ 44. Kg1 Rf1+ 45. Kg2
Rg5+ 46. Kh2 Ng4+ 47. Qxg4 Rxg4 48. Kh3 Kg5 49. Kh2 e1=Q 50. Kh3 Rh1#) 38...
Rg4 39. Qe3 Rh5+ (39... Rh5+ 40. Qh3 Rxh3+ 41. Kxh3 Kf5 42. f4 exf3 43. Kh2 f2
44. c4 f1=Q 45. c5 Qg2#) 0-1

