Nf6 5. Qe2 O-O 6. c3 (6. O-O c5 $11) 6... c5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d3 h6 {Prevents
intrusion on g5} 9. Be3 (9. a4 a6 $11) 9... a6 {Secures b5} 10. a3 {
Consolidates b4} b5 {Black threatens to win material: b5xc4} 11. Ba2 Bb7 (11...
d5 12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Nbd2 $11) 12. Rd1 Qc7 (12... d5 13. exd5 Nxd5 14. Nbd2 $11
) 13. Nbd2 Rad8 14. Nf1 (14. b4 cxb4 15. axb4 d5 16. exd5 Nxd5 $11) 14... Rfe8
15. Ng3 Bc8 (15... d5 $11) 16. Nf5 (16. b4 $142 $14 {is the best option White
has}) 16... Bxf5 $17 17. exf5 d5 18. Nh4 c4 19. Nf3 $2 (19. dxc4 bxc4 20. Nf3
Na5 $17) 19... e4 $4 {hands over the advantage to the opponent} (19... cxd3
$142 {makes sure everything is clear} 20. Qd2 Qd7 $19) 20. dxe4 $17 Nxe4 {
Black has a new backward pawn: d5.} 21. Nd4 Bxa3 (21... Bg5 $142 22. Re1 Nc5
$17) 22. Qc2 $2 (22. bxa3 $142 {would keep White in the game} Nxc3 23. Qb2 Nxd1
24. Rxd1 Nxd4 25. Bxd4 $11 (25. Qxd4 $143 Re4 26. Qb6 Qxb6 27. Bxb6 Rde8 $19))
22... Bd6 23. Nf3 Be5 (23... Ne7 $5 24. g4 $19) 24. Nxe5 Nxe5 25. Bb1 Nd3 26.
Rxa6 $4 {White has lost his nerve... understandable when you consider his
position.} (26. Rxd3 cxd3 27. Qxd3 $17) 26... Rd6 {Black threatens to win
material: Rd6xa6} (26... d4 $142 {and Black has triumphed} 27. Bxd4 Rxd4 28.
cxd4 Nexf2 $19) 27. Ra7 (27. Ra2 Qb8 28. Ba7 Qc8 29. Rxd3 cxd3 30. Qxd3 b4 $17
(30... Qxf5 $6 31. f3 $11)) 27... Qd8 (27... Qb8 $5 28. Bd4 Rf6 $17) 28. Rxd3 (
28. Qe2 Nexf2 29. Rf1 d4 30. cxd4 Qb8 $15) 28... cxd3 $15 29. Qxd3 Qh4 (29...
Rd7 $142 $15 {and Black can hope to survive}) 30. Qxb5 $16 Red8 (30... Rdd8 31.
Bd3 $16) 31. Qd3 (31. Bd3 Qf6 $16) 31... Rf6 (31... R6d7 $142 $14) 32. f3 $4 {
throwing away the advantage} (32. Qd4 $142 Rxf5 33. c4 $16) 32... Qe1+ $17 33.
Kh2 Ng3 34. Bg1 Nxf5 35. g4 $4 {causes even greater problems} (35. Bc2 $142 $17
) 35... Qg3+ 36. Kh1 Qxh3+ 37. Bh2 Ng3+ (37... Re6 38. Re7 Rxe7 39. Qd1 Nh4 40.
Qe2 Rxe2 41. Bh7+ Kxh7 42. Kg1 Qg2#) 38. Kg1 $19 g6 (38... Ne4 $142 {seems
even better} 39. Qe2 Rxf3 $19) 39. Ba2 (39. Re7 Rb8 40. b4 $19) 39... Re8 40.
Qd1 (40. Ra8 {hardly improves anything} Rxa8 41. Kf2 Qxh2+ 42. Ke3 Rxa2 43.
Qxd5 Qxb2 44. Kd3 Qe2+ 45. Kd4 Ra4+ 46. Kc5 Ra5+ 47. Kd4 Rf4+ 48. Qe4 Nxe4 49.
fxe4 Qxe4#) 40... Re2 (40... Re2 41. Ra8+ Kg7 42. Rg8+ Kxg8 43. Qxe2 Nxe2+ 44.
